reshold $\\sim 5 M_\\odot$pc$^{-2}$. At scales $>120$ pc surface SFR densities\ndetermined by using CO data and UV flux, $\\Sigma_{\\rm SFR, UV}/\\Sigma_{\\rm SFR,\ncl}$, demonstrate a discrepancy about a factor of 3. We argue that this may be\noriginated from overestimating (constant) values of conversion factor, star\nformation efficiency or UV calibration used in our analysis.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Feb 2017 22:23:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-12"}
